# @param {Integer[]} nums1
# @param {Integer[]} nums2
# @param {Integer} x
# @return {Integer}
def minimum_time(nums1, nums2, x)
  n = nums1.size
  prefix_sums = [0] * (n + 1)
  0.upto(n - 1) { |i| prefix_sums[i + 1] = prefix_sums[i] + nums1[i] }
  max_efficiency = Array.new(n)
  max_efficiency[n - 1] = nums1[n - 1] / nums2[n - 1].to_f
  (n - 2).downto(0) { |i| max_efficiency[i] = [max_efficiency[i + 1], nums1[i] / nums2[i].to_f].max }

  min_time = Float::INFINITY
  sum = 0
  nums1.each_with_index do |num, i|
    sum += num
    next_sum = sum
    time = i + 1
    if sum > x
      left = 0
      right = max_efficiency[i]
      while left < right
        mid = (left + right) / 2
        next_sum = sum
        (i + 1).upto(n - 1) { |j| next_sum -= [nums1[j] - mid * nums2[j], 0].max }
        if next_sum <= x
          right = mid
        else
          left = mid + 0.00001
        end
      end
      time += left
    end
    min_time = [min_time, time].min if next_sum <= x
  end

  min_time == Float::INFINITY ? -1 : min_time.ceil
end
